level.text:
Products classified by the United States Environmental Protection Agency (&#8220;U.S. EPA&#8221;) as exempt from regulation under section 25(b) of the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide and Rodenticide Act, approved October 21, 1972 (86 Stat.
        997; 7 U.S.C. § 136w(b)), when used according to District-approved label instructions, because the products meet all of the criteria set forth in 40 C.F.R. § 152.25, contain only the active ingredients listed in 40 C.F.R. § 152.25(f)(1) (2008,
        or as amended), and include only the inert ingredients described in 40 C.F.R. § 152.25(f)(2) and listed in the most current List 4A (4A Inerts List), which may be found at http://www.epa.gov/opprd001/inerts/inerts-list4Acas.pdf;
